The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Sourav may play

A STAFF REPORTER

Calcutta: Its not confirmed, but former India captain Sourav Ganguly is almost certain to be playing for Bengal in the National Twenty20 Championship. 

Hes most likely to play, CAB president Prasun Mukherjee told The Telegraph on Monday evening after a closed-door meeting with Sourav which lasted nearly an hour. 

Bengals first match is against Tamil Nadu on April 15. They then come up against Haryana (April 16), Madhya Pradesh (April 17) and Mumbai (April 19). All matches will be in Ahmedabad. 




